1169
01:27:43,050 --> 01:27:46,720
We started using a technique
called photogrametry...

1170
01:27:46,971 --> 01:27:50,850
...where we were gonna create
large chunks of the city...

1171
01:27:51,058 --> 01:27:56,939
...based on multiple-positioned
camera photographs of New York.

1172
01:27:57,189 --> 01:28:02,570
It turned out that that technique
didn't provide us enough resolution.

1173
01:28:02,820 --> 01:28:06,490
Meaning that the buildings
we created that way...

1174
01:28:06,740 --> 01:28:12,955
...didn't have enough detail in them
for the camera to get close to them.

1175
01:28:13,164 --> 01:28:16,292
We then decided instead
of doing that...

1176
01:28:16,500 --> 01:28:19,420
...to use conventional...

1177
01:28:20,337 --> 01:28:22,756
...surveyors' instruments...

1178
01:28:23,007 --> 01:28:28,095
...to create a mathematical model
of buildings in much higher detail...

1179
01:28:28,345 --> 01:28:34,643
...and use still photographs of the
surfaces of those buildings to be...

1180
01:28:34,810 --> 01:28:37,688
...stretched back
onto that geometry.

1181
01:28:37,938 --> 01:28:42,985
We had the shape of the building and
we had a picture of the surfaces...

1182
01:28:43,152 --> 01:28:47,448
...on the building. We placed
those surfaces onto the building.

1183
01:28:47,615 --> 01:28:50,284
It's called mapping.

1184
01:28:50,534 --> 01:28:54,997
And as you look at this...
As we continues through this...

1185
01:28:55,206 --> 01:29:00,336
...you're gonna see extensive
use of this technique.

1186
01:29:00,586 --> 01:29:05,966
We had buildings in the middle ground,
foreground, and in the distance.

1187
01:29:06,217 --> 01:29:12,806
Some were in original photography
and some were added in after the fact.

1188
01:29:13,015 --> 01:29:16,977
The other weakness
photogrametry had was you tend...

1189
01:29:17,186 --> 01:29:20,314
...to get the built
in lighting of the day...

1190
01:29:20,523 --> 01:29:23,484
...so it depends on
how overcast it is...

1191
01:29:23,692 --> 01:29:27,905
...the sun's angle, what time of day.
You don't have leeway.

1192
01:29:28,113 --> 01:29:31,992
Our buildings had to hold up
for different sun angles...

1193
01:29:32,243 --> 01:29:34,328
...and different times of day.

1194
01:29:34,578 --> 01:29:41,085
So our main texture painter guy,
